data: {"type":"response.output_item.done","item":{"type":"message","id":"msg_0552e1a2b15e39a8006998ce2c28948194bc0ff8d8b9940859","agent_reference":{"type":"agent_reference","name":"MyAgent","version":"282"},"response_id":"resp_0552e1a2b15e39a8006998cde4fea881949c403c0b7e42dbda","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"Foundry Agent Service is Microsoft’s managed “agent runtime” inside **Microsoft Foundry** for building, deploying, and operating **AI agents** in production.\n\n### What it does\nIt stitches together the core pieces you need to move beyond a demo chatbot into an operational agent system:\n\n- **Runs and manages agent conversations** (threads/runs) and the agent’s lifecycle across dev → prod.\n- **Orchestrates tool use** (the model decides when to call tools; the service coordinates those calls).\n- **Connects agents to models + tools + frameworks** in one place, so you don’t have to build as much runtime plumbing yourself.\n- **Applies trust/safety and governance** as part of the runtime (for example, content safety enforcement).\n- **Integrates with enterprise platform needs** like identity, networking, and observability so agents can be production-ready. 【5:0†source】\n\n### How “agents” work in this context\nAn agent is more than a chat interface: it can **make decisions**, **invoke tools**, and **participate in workflows**—sometimes autonomously, sometimes with humans or other agents involved. Foundry Agent Service is the layer that helps make those behaviors reliable and manageable in real systems. 【5:0†source】\n\n### Tools you can plug into agents\nFoundry Agent Service supports a catalog of built-in and extensible tools, typically in two buckets: 【5:1†source】\n\n- **Knowledge tools** (to ground the agent in data): e.g., **Azure AI Search**, file search, Microsoft Fabric, and also web grounding options.\n- **Action tools** (to do work): e.g., **Azure Logic Apps**, OpenAPI tools, **MCP** endpoints, function calling, Azure Functions, and more. 【5:1†source】\n\n### Web grounding options (two examples)\n- **Grounding with Bing Search**: lets agents incorporate real-time public web data and return responses with citations (while not exposing raw retrieved content directly). 【5:3†source】\n- **Grounding with Bing Custom Search (preview)**: limits web retrieval to a configurable set of domains you choose (useful for “only search these trusted sites”). 【5:2†source】\n\nIf you tell me whether you’re using the “new” or “classic” Foundry portal/agents API—and what you’re trying to build (support agent, document automation, ticket triage, etc.)—I can point you to the right quickstart path and recommended tool setup.","annotations":[{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/overview?view=foundry-classic","start_index":860,"end_index":872,"title":"What is Foundry Agent Service? - Microsoft Foundry"},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/overview?view=foundry-classic","start_index":1210,"end_index":1222,"title":"What is Foundry Agent Service? - Microsoft Foundry"},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/overview?view=foundry-classic","start_index":1360,"end_index":1372,"title":"What are tools in Foundry Agent Service - Microsoft Foundry"},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/overview?view=foundry-classic","start_index":1657,"end_index":1669,"title":"What are tools in Foundry Agent Service - Microsoft Foundry"},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/bing-grounding?view=foundry-classic","start_index":1885,"end_index":1897,"title":"How to use Grounding with Bing Search in Foundry Agent Service ..."},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/agents/how-to/tools-classic/bing-custom-search?view=foundry-classic","start_index":2062,"end_index":2074,"title":"How to use Custom Bing Search with Foundry Agent Service - Azure OpenAI ..."}],"logprobs":[]}],"status":"completed"},"output_index":2,"sequence_number":504}

